{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014TiKaUeqW8bG64cbQzuhX9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The logs still show the old error. The issue is that the ConfigMap volume in the pod is still showing the old content (the bad concatenation from before). Kubernetes ConfigMap volumes update asynchronously - the kubelet syncs them within the configured sync period (default 1 minute). Since the pod is in CrashLoopBackOff, it keeps using whatever content is currently in the mounted volume.\n\nBut wait - in CrashLoopBackOff, the pod RESTARTS but the volumes are mounted from the same pod spec. ConfigMaps mounted as volumes ARE synced by the kubelet, but only when the pod is running. Since the pod keeps crashing immediately on startup (ES fails to start), maybe the ConfigMap volume hasn't been updated yet.\nActually, ConfigMap volumes do get updated even during CrashLoopBackOff - the kubelet syncs them periodically, typically every 60 seconds but potentially up to 2 minutes. The error message still shows the malformed certificate from my first update, which means the second fix I applied a few minutes ago probably hasn't synced yet. I should delete the pod to force a fresh restart and pick up the corrected ConfigMap content.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":661,"cache_read_input_tokens":52847,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":661},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6e1741cd-b326-4c00-995c-173471f3540c","uuid":"e33f8704-96e8-4151-a02a-5999f779d1c0","request_id":"req_011CbyDPDbVrCm3aCH8rk8aN"}
