{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GZ3teJ1VLg3AghzqudcSkX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The oracle passes: **\"Transport CA trust verified\"**.\n\nThe cluster is restored. Here's what was wrong and what I did:\n\n**Root cause:** The `es-transport-ca-bundle` ConfigMap only contained CA1's certificate. `es-cluster-2` uses a node certificate signed by CA2, so when it tried to establish transport TLS connections to `es-cluster-0` and `es-cluster-1`, those nodes rejected it with `bad_certificate` — they didn't trust CA2.\n\n**Fix:**\n1. Extracted CA2's certificate from the `es-transport-ca2` secret\n2. Updated `es-transport-ca-bundle` to contain both CA1 and CA2 certificates (properly newline-separated in a valid PEM bundle)\n3. Triggered a rolling restart of the StatefulSet so all pods mounted the updated CA bundle\n\nAll 3 nodes now form a healthy cluster with mutual transport TLS trust across both CAs."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":511,"cache_read_input_tokens":66605,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":511},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6e1741cd-b326-4c00-995c-173471f3540c","uuid":"503c6ccf-ddcb-43a1-b5af-afbae8b16c8c","request_id":"req_011CbyDYPBhiCYAFu9XdKwZ4"}
